column1: Narrative
column2: Not enough money for basic necessities (food, clothing, transportation, housing, healthcare etc.)
column3: Not enough money for wants (entertainment and recreation)

column1: Today was one of those days where everything seemed to go wrong. Waking up to an empty wallet, I realized I didn't have enough money to cover my basic necessities. Skipping breakfast, I rushed to catch the crowded train, praying I wouldn't get caught without a ticket. As classes went by, my growling stomach became a constant reminder of my financial struggles. With each passing hour, the weight of not being able to afford proper healthcare or even a decent meal seemed to crush me. But amidst these challenges, I remained determined to find a way to overcome these daily hassles and create a better future for myself.

Today was a tough day. Waking up with an empty stomach, I realized I didn't have enough money for basic necessities like food, clothing, transportation, housing, and even healthcare. It's a constant struggle to make ends meet as an undergraduate student at DLSU. Despite working part-time, expenses seem to always outweigh my income. But I remain hopeful that things will improve. I know that with perseverance and determination, I will find a way to overcome these daily hassles and create a better future for myself.

Today was just another day of juggling my responsibilities as a DLSU undergraduate student. However, the constant worry about not having enough money for basic necessities always weighs me down. The reality of not having enough funds for healthcare or even basic clothing adds to the daily challenges. Despite these daily hassles, I strive to stay focused on my studies and make the most out of the opportunities that DLSU provides.

So today was a typical day of being a struggling undergraduate student at DLSU. Waking up, I realized that my bank account was nearly empty, leaving me with not enough money for even the basic necessities. As I rummaged through my closet, I found myself wearing the same clothes I had worn for the past week. Skipping breakfast, I hopped on the crowded public transportation to make it to class on time. Throughout the day, thoughts of how I'll afford my next meal, pay my rent, and cover my healthcare expenses lingered in my mind. It's a constant battle, but I know that perseverance will eventually guide me through these daily financial hassles.
